  "prompt": "How long can a milkshake last out of the fridge?",
  "response": "A milkshake can typically last about 1-2 hours at room temperature before it starts to spoil. This is due to the dairy content, which is prone to bacterial growth when not kept cold. To ensure safety and maintain quality, it's best to consume a milkshake shortly after it's made or keep it refrigerated. If left out for longer than two hours, it's advisable to discard it to prevent the risk of foodborne illness.",
